Definition: used especially of ideas or principles) deeply rooted
Example: firmly fixed or held; deep-rooted prejudice; deep-seated differences of opinion; implanted convictions; ingrained habits of a lifetime; a deeply planted need
Synonyms: deep-seated, implanted, ingrained, planted, used, especially, of, ideas, or, principles, deeply, rooted, firmly, fixed, held, prejudice, differences, opinion, convictions, habits, a, lifetime, need
Category: adj.all
